approach: DP (Bottom-Up): Formulate as a 0/1 Knapsack Problem. Iterate over all `nums` and update `dp` to be `dp[i] or dp[i - num]`. For each `num`, traverse `i` backwards to prevent using the same element twice.
time_complexity: O(n x s) where n = number of numbers, s = target sum
space_complexity: O(n) where n = number of numbers
